<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="322" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1072,431,456]" box="[151,1072,431,456]" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">
<typeStatus box="[151,201,432,456]" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Whitehead &amp; Steiner 1994" authorityName="Whitehead &amp; Steiner" authorityYear="1994" box="[294,896,431,456]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albifasciata" subGenus="Albiviva">
<emphasis box="[294,383,432,456]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Rediviva</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[398,482,432,456]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Albiviva</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[497,617,432,456]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">albifasciata</emphasis>
Whitehead &amp; Steiner 1994
</taxonomicName>
, designated here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,497,1135]" box="[151,730,497,523]" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">
The only species in this subgenus is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Whitehead &amp; Steiner" authorityYear="1994" box="[559,723,497,523]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albifasciata">
<emphasis box="[559,723,497,523]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">R. albifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="322" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,497,1135]" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,532,559]" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The subgenus is monotypic and just contains 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Whitehead &amp; Steiner" authorityYear="1994" box="[855,1020,533,559]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albifasciata">
<emphasis box="[855,1020,533,559]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">R. albifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which is the smallest species of the genus (
<quantity box="[231,342,569,595]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" unit="mm" value="9.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="8.0">8–10 mm</quantity>
). Males can be recognized by a combination of the following characters: median lobes of S7 spatulate (
<figureCitation box="[206,287,605,632]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1652,1677]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1626]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,181,1627]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Rediviva (Albiviva) albifasciata Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♂: a. metasomal sternum 8, apical plate; b. metasomal ster- num 7, dorsal view. R. (s. str.) macgregori Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♂: c. metasomal sternum 8, apical plate; d. metasomal sternum 7, dorsal view. R. (s. str.) longimanus Michener ♂: e. metasomal sternum 7, dorsal view (ll: lateral lobe; ml: median lobe); f. metasomal sternum 7, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889571" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889571/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
) (not apically broadened in other subgenera); lateral lobes large and smooth, papillate on basal third (in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez, 2020" authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez" authorityYear="2020" box="[151,254,641,667]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Gigaviva">
<emphasis box="[151,254,641,667]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Gigaviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lateral lobes missing; not papillate in other subgenera); apical plate of S8 distally straight (
<figureCitation box="[1266,1345,641,667]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1652,1677]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1626]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,181,1627]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Rediviva (Albiviva) albifasciata Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♂: a. metasomal sternum 8, apical plate; b. metasomal ster- num 7, dorsal view. R. (s. str.) macgregori Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♂: c. metasomal sternum 8, apical plate; d. metasomal sternum 7, dorsal view. R. (s. str.) longimanus Michener ♂: e. metasomal sternum 7, dorsal view (ll: lateral lobe; ml: median lobe); f. metasomal sternum 7, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889571" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889571/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
) (apical margin deeply cleft in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez, 2020" authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez" authorityYear="2020" box="[404,507,677,703]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Gigaviva">
<emphasis box="[404,507,677,703]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Gigaviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; apically notched, emarginate or semi-circular in other subgenera).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,497,1135]" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">
Females show a unique combination of a broadened hind tibia and basitarsus with the scopa consisting of densely plumose pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[490,567,749,776]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[192,1394,182,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[192,1395,181,1864]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rediviva (Albiviva) albifasciata Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: a. metasoma with distinct white apical hair bands. R. (s. str.) whiteheadi Kuhlmann ♀: b. metasoma with indistinct yellowish apical hair bands. R. (Redivivoides) capensis (Kuhlmann) ♀: c. hind leg. R. (Deriviva) intermedia Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: d. front leg, coxa with apical hairy spine (s). R. (Deriviva) intermixta Cockerell ♀: e. hind basitarsus with shiny scale-like projection; f. hind leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889569" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889569/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Fig. 3f</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName box="[620,763,749,775]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Redivivoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[620,763,749,775]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Redivivoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
hind tibia not broadened and without plumose pubescence), bidentate mandible (tridentate in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez, 2020" authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez" authorityYear="2020" box="[529,632,785,811]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" status="subgen. nov." subGenus="Gigaviva">
<emphasis box="[529,632,785,811]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Gigaviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and small shiny scale-like projection on the distal-dorsal angle of the hind basitarsus (smaller than in 
<figureCitation box="[504,582,821,847]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[192,1394,182,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[192,1395,181,1864]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rediviva (Albiviva) albifasciata Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: a. metasoma with distinct white apical hair bands. R. (s. str.) whiteheadi Kuhlmann ♀: b. metasoma with indistinct yellowish apical hair bands. R. (Redivivoides) capensis (Kuhlmann) ♀: c. hind leg. R. (Deriviva) intermedia Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: d. front leg, coxa with apical hairy spine (s). R. (Deriviva) intermixta Cockerell ♀: e. hind basitarsus with shiny scale-like projection; f. hind leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889569" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889569/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
) (projection distinctly larger in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Whitehead &amp; Steiner" authorityYear="2001" box="[934,1086,821,847]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis box="[934,1086,821,847]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">R. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1099,1244,822,847]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermixta">
<emphasis box="[1099,1244,822,847]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">R. intermixta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1297,1407,821,847]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Redivivoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufipes">
R. 
<emphasis box="[1329,1407,821,847]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">rufipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuhlmann &amp; Jürgensen &amp; Michez" authorityYear="2020" box="[263,361,858,883]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Deriviva">
<emphasis box="[263,361,858,883]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Deriviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, missing in all other species) in combination with the small size and distinct white apical tergal hair bands (
<figureCitation box="[284,365,893,919]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1889,1914]" captionTargetBox="[192,1394,182,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[192,1395,181,1864]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rediviva (Albiviva) albifasciata Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: a. metasoma with distinct white apical hair bands. R. (s. str.) whiteheadi Kuhlmann ♀: b. metasoma with indistinct yellowish apical hair bands. R. (Redivivoides) capensis (Kuhlmann) ♀: c. hind leg. R. (Deriviva) intermedia Whitehead &amp; Steiner ♀: d. front leg, coxa with apical hairy spine (s). R. (Deriviva) intermixta Cockerell ♀: e. hind basitarsus with shiny scale-like projection; f. hind leg." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3889569" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3889569/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
) (less conspicuous yellowish or missing in all other subgenera) that only occur in this species. This is the only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1911" box="[330,428,929,955]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[330,428,929,955]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Rediviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species that collects oil in flowers of 
<taxonomicName box="[848,1010,929,955]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Colpias" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mollis">
<emphasis box="[848,1010,929,955]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Colpias mollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[1025,1222,929,956]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Scrophulariaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Steiner, K. E. &amp; Whitehead, V. B." pageId="4" pageNumber="322" pagination="53 - 66" refId="ref6570" refString="Steiner, K. E. &amp; Whitehead, V. B. (2002) Oil secretion and the pollination of Colpias mollis (Scrophulariaceae). Plant Systematics and Evolution, 235, 53 - 66. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00606 - 002 - 0216 - y" type="journal article" year="2002">Steiner &amp; Whitehead 2002</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kuhlmann, M. &amp; Hollens, H." box="[281,590,964,991]" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" pagination="561 - 573" refId="ref5935" refString="Kuhlmann, M. &amp; Hollens, H. (2015) Morphology of oil-collecting pilosity of female Rediviva bees (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Melittidae) reflects host plant use. Journal of Natural History, 49, 561 - 573. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222933.2014.939732" type="journal article" year="2015">Kuhlmann &amp; Hollens 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="322" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,497,1135]" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1001,1027]" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new subgeneric name is a combination of the first part of the specific epithet of the 
<typeStatus box="[1334,1382,1001,1027]" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Whitehead &amp; Steiner" authorityYear="1994" box="[202,365,1037,1063]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albifasciata">
<emphasis box="[202,365,1037,1063]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">R. albifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the last part of the generic name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1911" box="[786,884,1037,1063]" class="Insecta" family="Melittidae" genus="Rediviva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="322" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[786,884,1037,1063]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Rediviva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The gender of the name is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="322" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,497,1135]" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1072,1099]" pageId="4" pageNumber="322">Distribution.</emphasis>
The species is only known from the western part of the winter rainfall region (
<bibRefCitation author="Whitehead, V. B. &amp; Steiner, K. E." pageId="4" pageNumber="322" pagination="143 - 277" refId="ref6735" refString="Whitehead, V. B. &amp; Steiner, K. E. (2001) Oil-collecting bees of the winter rainfall area of South Africa (Melittidae, Rediviva). Annals of the South African Museum, 108, 143 - 277." type="journal article" year="2001">Whitehead &amp; Steiner 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
